sparql_query_kg2:
 Given the context and the entity/relation mappings, here's the SPARQL query for DBpedia to find all swimmers born in Moscow:

```sparql
PREFIX dbo: <http://dbpedia.org/ontology/>
PREFIX res: <http://dbpedia.org/resource/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?uri WHERE {
  ?uri rdf:type dbo:Swimmer ;
        dbo:birthPlace res:Moscow .
}
```

This query will retrieve all distinct URIs of swimmers who were born in Moscow according to the DBpedia knowledge graph.

